        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 4:09PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 409 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Central Mills, or 15 miles southeast of Uniontown, moving northeast
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Selma, Orrville, Bogue Chitto, Central Mills, Memorial Stadium,
Marion Junction, Dallas County Horse Arena, Potter Station, Dannelly
Reservoir, Skyharbor Airport, Radford, Whites Bluff, Safford,
Summerfield, Hazen, Suttle, Selma University, and Crumptonia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
